The paper discusses the use of deep learning in tasks related to visual intelligence and cognitive computing, specifically in the context of subitizing and natural number comprehension. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the learning method used in deep learning and the use of cognitive priors, which are topics that fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also touches on the computational machinery used in deep learning, which could potentially fall under the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
